      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RED HOT RANGOON (6) chased the lead early from the inside draw but took over turning to score (22.72) at The Gardens in a Grade 5 over 400m. The form out of her last race has been franked. Has hit winning form and can measure up again. FRANK CHANA (2) jumped from this box and scrambled home to a narrow Grade 5 win at Taree Super Track over 300m latest (18.13). With a good start should be able to take advantage of the low draw. Bold showing expected again. MILA'S MAGIC (1) has a moderate overall strike-rate. Better run when finding the frame last time though, finishing third (23.37) at this track. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Leading player again. HECTIC BLUE (8) should be thereabouts despite an unplaced run here most recently.",
